27/01/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- <I>Milliyet</I> reported Sunday (26 January) that Turkey has agreed to let US troops transit the country if there is a military operation against Iraq. 
Though military centres would be established along the border to provide logistical support, US troops would not be stationed in the country. 
According to the newspaper, the agreement will be discussed Friday by Turkey's National Security Council and then forwarded to parliament for approval. 
Prime Minister Abdullah Gul has insisted that Turkey would oppose unilateral US actions, especially without a resolution from the UN Security Council. 
(AP, Anadolu Agency, AFP, Dunya, TRT - 26/01/03)
